--- Descriptor Score Parameters: Footprint Similarity Score ---
descriptor_fps_score_use_footprint_reference_mol2            yes
descriptor_fps_score_footprint_reference_mol2_filename       lig.mol2
descriptor_fps_score_foot_compare_type                       d
descriptor_fps_score_foot_comp_all_residue                   no
descriptor_fps_score_choose_foot_range_type                  threshold
-------------------------------------------------------------
You chose to use a residue range that is defined by only residues that
have magnitudes that excede the specified thresholds (the 3 following
parameters).  Each footprint type will have a distinct residue range.
The union of both the ref. and pose ranges will define the
evaluated range.
-------------------------------------------------------------
descriptor_fps_score_vdw_threshold                           1
descriptor_fps_score_es_threshold                            1
descriptor_fps_score_hb_threshold                            0.5
descriptor_fps_score_use_remainder                           yes
descriptor_fps_score_receptor_filename                       rec.mol2
descriptor_fps_score_vdw_att_exp                             6
descriptor_fps_score_vdw_rep_exp                             12
descriptor_fps_score_vdw_rep_rad_scale                       1
descriptor_fps_score_use_distance_dependent_dielectric       yes
descriptor_fps_score_dielectric                              4.0
descriptor_fps_score_vdw_fp_scale                            0
descriptor_fps_score_es_fp_scale                             0
descriptor_fps_score_hb_fp_scale                             0

--- Descriptor Score Weights ---
descriptor_weight_cont_score                                 1
descriptor_weight_fps_score                                  0

Using these settings, the Descriptor Score function takes the form:
Descriptor_Score = (1 * Continuous_Score) + (0 * Footprint_Similarity_Score)

